<title>USA: Pier 1 gets payment in suit settlement.</title>
<headline>Pier 1 gets payment in suit settlement.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pier 1 Imports Inc has received a payment of $7.5 million from the commodities brokerage firm invloved in the $19.5 million of trading losses the company announced in December 1995, Pier 1 said in an 8K filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.</p>
<p>It said the settlement has been approved by the District Court in Tarrant County, Texas, where a Pier 1 stockholder filed a derivative suit on behalf of the company in January 1996. The company had filed a third-party claim against the brokerage firm.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610))</p>
